class Solution {
public:
    int minInsertions(string s) {
        int balance = 0;
        int insertions = 0;
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == '(') {
                balance++;
            } else {
                if (balance > 0) {
                    balance--;
                } else {
                    insertions++;
                }
            }
        }
        insertions += 2 * balance;
        return insertions;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, maintaining a balance of opening and closing parentheses. When encountering a closing parenthesis without a matching opening parenthesis, it increments the insertions count. Finally, it adds twice the remaining balance to the insertions count, as each opening parenthesis needs two closing parentheses to match.

